The police yesterday arraigned a member of the House of Representatives for Port Harcourt City Local Government Constituency II, Chinyere Igwe, at the Federal High Court sitting in Port Harcourt for alleged money laundering. Igwe, a campaigner for the presidential candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) Atiku Abubakar, was arrested by the police in Port Harcourt hours to the presidential election with $498,000 and a distribution list. The lawmaker, according to the charge sheet, was seen in possession of $498,000 without reporting to the Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN). Igwe pleaded not guilty. Justice Stephen Daylop-Pam adjourned the case till March 14.